This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as Chinese word segmentation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural model for the task. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for language processing. The paper also mentions the use of character embeddings, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model's performance on benchmark datasets, which could categorize it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
